  <title>Install Drivers</title>

  <p>Vanilla Control Center allows the user to install available drivers from the <gui>ubuntu-drivers</gui> package.</p>
  
<media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/vanilla-control-center.png"/>
 
  <p>The steps for installing drivers are:</p>

  <list>
    <item><p>Open the <app>Vanilla Control Center</app>.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click on the required Driver to install from the <gui>Drivers</gui> tab.</p></item>
    
    <media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/vanilla-control-center-apply.png"/>
    <item><p>Click on the <gui>Apply Changes</gui> button on the top right corner.</p></item>
  </list>
  
  <media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/vanilla-control-center-apply.png"/>

  <p>Once the changes are applied, the installation of the <gui>Drivers</gui> will begin in a separate window.</p>
  
<media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/vanilla-control-center-installation.png"/>

  <p>After the installation of the Drivers, reboot your system. You have now successfully installed the required drivers.</p>
